2026-05-04 | Check if Binary Representation is Palindrome

	Question
Return true if binary representation is palindrome.
	Approach
1.	Find highest set bit (left pointer)  
2.	Set right pointer at LSB  
3.	Compare bits:
		left bit vs right bit  
4.	If mismatch → return false  
5.	Move inward:
		left--, right++  
6.	If all match → return true  
	Time Complexity
	O(log n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool isBinaryPalindrome(int n) {
        int left = 31;
        // find highest set bit
        while(left >= 0 && ((n >> left) & 1) == 0){
            left--;
        }
        int right = 0;
        while(left > right){
            int lbit = (n >> left) & 1;
            int rbit = (n >> right) & 1;
            if(lbit != rbit)
                return false;
            left--;
            right++;
        }
        return true;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Instead of converting to string:
		compare bits directly  
This saves space and keeps solution efficient.
